3) cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper uses a belief-propagation approach, which is commonly used in network analysis. 
4) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of different decoding algorithms. 
5) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of a machine learning technique (Bayesian Approximate Message Passing decoder).
